description:
&lt;p&gt;There is an exciting opportunity to come and work as part of the Neurodisability service at Great Ormond Street Hospital. We are looking for a Paediatric Nurse with neurology experience to join our specialist service which encompassess Sturge Weber, Neurofibromatosis types and other Neurocutaneous conditions.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As the CNS your role will include&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Providing information about Sturge-Weber syndrome and taking responsibility for this cohort of patients incorporating care co-ordination remit as required.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Providing nursing leadership, expertise, advice and support regarding medical management, therapy and/or learning.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Act as a resource to children and families and liaison with local services.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Involvement in audit and research&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As the CNS you must possess excellent communication and strong leadership skills to ensure the families are provided with support and a smooth patient journey.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;This CNS post is a 0.4 WTE / 15hrs per week&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Name Lucy Thomas Job title Matron Telephone number 020 7405 9200 ext 6362&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
